HEADWORD: Hackly
<hw>Hac"kly</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧k"l⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Hackle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rough or broken, as if
hacked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Having fine, short, and sharp
points on the surface; <as>as, the <ex>hackly</ex> fracture of metallic
iron</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hackman</ent>⟦br⟧
